      "content": "Government regulation of the internet infringes on personal autonomy because it imposes external control over individuals' choices and access to information. When the state dictates what can be shared or accessed online, it undermines the individual's right to self-govern their own information consumption, which is a cornerstone of personal freedom. This intrusion into personal decision-making erodes the foundation of a free society, where individuals should have the liberty to seek, share, and evaluate information without government interference. By prioritizing collective control over individual autonomy, such regulation compromises the very essence of free speech and personal liberty.",
